</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BBB522EFF9BFFB5C9F5FE36FB50B633" blockId="14.[136,1451,396,599]" pageId="14" pageNumber="207">
<emphasis id="B9708E3CFF9BFFB5C9F5FE36FE13B674" bold="true" box="[189,429,501,528]" pageId="14" pageNumber="207">Taxonomic notes:—</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="4C0429ADFF9BFFB5C8E5FE35FD3DB66B" authorityName="Kunth" authorityYear="1817" box="[429,643,502,528]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Euphorbiaceae" genus="Euphorbia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malpighiales" pageId="14" pageNumber="207" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="serpens">
<emphasis id="B9708E3CFF9BFFB5C8E5FE35FD3DB66B" box="[429,643,502,528]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="207">Euphorbia serpens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differs from all other prostrate 
<taxonomicName id="4C0429ADFF9BFFB5CAA6FE35FBD8B674" authorityName="Linnaeus" authorityYear="1753" box="[1006,1126,502,528]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Euphorbiaceae" genus="Euphorbia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malpighiales" pageId="14" pageNumber="207" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B9708E3CFF9BFFB5CAA6FE35FBD8B674" box="[1006,1126,502,528]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="207">Euphorbia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in the state of 
<collectingRegion id="49C09CCCFF9BFFB5CC5CFE35FA39B674" box="[1300,1415,502,528]" country="Brazil" name="Sao Paulo" pageId="14" pageNumber="207">São Paulo</collectingRegion>
by its complete absence of an indumentum, fused, whitish triangular intrapetiolar stipules, cyathial glands with petaloid appendages well developed and equal in size, presence of adventitious roots and a smooth seed coat.
</paragraph>
